TITLE: Converting Local Time to UTC in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to convert a local date-time value to UTC using the date-fns-tz library. It retrieves the picked date and the target time zone, then converts the time to UTC format before posting it to a server.
SOURCE: https://github.com/DouyinFE/semi-design/blob/main/packages/semi-ui/datePicker/contributing.md#2025-04-12_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
"import { zonedTimeToUtc } from 'date-fns-tz'\n\nconst date = getDatePickerValue() // e.g. 2014-06-25 10:00:00 (picked in any time zone)\nconst timeZone = getTimeZoneValue() // e.g. America/Los_Angeles\n\nconst utcDate = zonedTimeToUtc(date, timeZone) // In June 10am in Los Angeles is 5pm UTC\n\npostToServer(utcDate.toISOString(), timeZone) // post 2014-06-25T17:00:00.000Z, America/Los_Angeles"
```

